fieldNotes: Dunes of white sand, in a distance of 1-2Km from the shore. Open tree & scrub woodland with xeromorphic or semisucculent leaves.Some trees up to 4m, mostly Clusiaceae, Ericaceae, Bignoniaceae, Rubiaceae, Leguminosae, and others. Low palms with large underground-trunks, terrestrial Bromeliaceae & Orchidaceae, small Velloziaceae frequent. Valleys sometimes overflood, maily covered with Cyperaceae, Eriocaulaceae and Lentibulariaceae. Some vines and no epiphytes.
